South African petrochemical firm Sasol jumped more than 7% in early trade, hitting a two-month high. Shares were trading 4.66% higher at R399.34 at the close in Johannesburg.OPEC and non-OPEC agree first global oil pact since 2001 to reduce supply of oil after two years of low prices.Brent crude, the international benchmark for oil prices, rose by as much as 6.5% to an 18-month high.